BabNBPar1 i 6'b. [... MUL-M]EŠ mi-qit {d}be-en?#-nu!#(IGI?#)
#note: See @bib{fromebllab0044@151 fn. 54}: “The final oblique of the @akk{BAD} sign seems to overlap with the initial horizontal of the @akk{EN} sign.”

#tr.en: be you an image of Namtar, be you an image of the devil, be you any Evil that exists,
7. %n lū ṣalam namtari lū ṣalam gallê lū mimma lemnu ša šuma nabû
